Description: Hardy, green-and-gray hummingbird; males with rosy-pink crown & gorget.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; most visible at feeders and winter-blooming shrubs.
Favorite foods: Flower nectar, small insects; sugar-water (1:4) at feeders.
Typical habitat: Yards with flowers/feeders, parks, forest edges.

Description: Tiny, fiery-orange (male) migratory hummingbird; very territorial.
Favorite foods: Flower nectar, small insects; will use nectar feeders.
Typical habitat: Woodland edges, gardens with tubular flowers.

Description: Friendly, black-capped, white-cheeked songbird; common at feeders.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; active mornings, vocal in spring.
Favorite foods: Seeds (black oil sunflower), suet, insects, berries.

Description: Small chickadee with rich chestnut back and sides; coastal forests.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; travels with mixed flocks fall–winter.
Typical habitat: Coniferous and mixed forests, forested neighborhoods.

Description: Slate-hooded sparrow with white outer tail feathers; ground feeder.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; biggest yard flocks in fall–winter.
Typical habitat: Woodland edges, brushy yards; forages on the ground.

Description: Striking black hood, rufous sides, white spots; scratch-feeding sparrow.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; most visible at dawn/dusk under shrubs.
Favorite foods: Seeds and insects; spilled seed under feeders.

Description: Brown streaky sparrow with a central breast spot; rich, varied song.
Familiar gray bird with orange breast; exuberant dawn singer.
Typical habitat: Lawns, parks, forest edges, berry shrubs.

Description: Large woodpecker; brown with black spots; flashing red underwings.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; often feeding on ground ants.
Favorite foods: Ants, beetles; suet at feeders, fruits.
Typical habitat: Open woods, yards with trees/snags, lawns.

Description: Tiny tree-climbing bird; nasal yank-yank call; rusty underparts.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; irruptions bring many in some winters.
Typical habitat: Coniferous forests, yards with mature conifers.

Description: Brown wren with bold white eyebrow; active tail-flicking.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; sings from shrubs in spring.
Favorite foods: Insects and spiders; rarely uses feeders.

Description: Tiny, gray flocking bird; travels in chatty groups through shrubs.
Red-faced (male) finch; streaky brown female; common at feeders.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; active mid-morning and late afternoon.

Description: Bright yellow (male breeding) finch; bouncy flight; sweet 'potato-chip' call.
Best time in Port Orchard: Year-round; most visible at nyjer/sunflower feeders spring–summer.
Typical habitat: Weedy fields, gardens, edges; feeder stations.

Description: Bold blue jay with dark crest; loud calls; often visits feeders.
